@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_RoleTopology> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_RoleTopology> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#RoleTopology> ;
    narr:childCount "10"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers how aswritten models *who occupies what* in an organization. The mainline distinction is firm and dated: a [role is an abstraction with its own module](narr:Narrative_OrgRolesAbstraction) that persists independently of the person filling it (Mar 2026, from PR 91), while an [actor is a specific person](narr:Narrative_ActorVsRoleAbstraction) — Tony, then a demo-call prospect — where multiple actors contribute to one role over time and assignment emerges from conversation, not static tags (Apr 2026). [Roles are first-class product concepts](narr:Claim_OrgRolesFirstClass), and the team itself is [staffed as perspectives on cadence](narr:Claim_TeamAsPerspectives) rather than full-time hires — Scarlet [needs no co-founder but a constellation](narr:Claim_NoCoFounderNeeded) (Mar 2026). A grounding case: the [practitioner occupies three transaction shapes at once](narr:Narrative_PractitionerThreeRoles) (supplier, customer, trust-broker) from one account (Apr 2026). Running underneath since May 2025 is the [Microsoft gatekeeper pattern](narr:Claim_MultiRoleCoordinationGatekeeper) — a centralized ground-truth mechanism flagged as *missing* — which by Apr 2026 [surfaces unresolved design questions](narr:Claim_GatekeeperDesignQuestionsOpen) rather than an answer. Concrete sales-role mechanics ([Tony influence vs a demo-call prospect direct](narr:Obs_DemoProspectVsTonyDivision)) ground the abstraction.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_GatekeeperDesignQuestionsOpen> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_MultiRoleCoordinationGatekeeper> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_NoCoFounderNeeded> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_OrgRolesFirstClass> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_TeamAsPerspectives> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ActorVsRoleAbstraction> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_OrgRolesAbstraction> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_PractitionerThreeRoles> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_DemoProspectVsTonyDivision> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_EnterpriseProspectHotelTactic> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "here the practitioner is simultaneously supplier, customer, and unpaid trust node, depending on which transaction is active" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_PractitionerThreeRoles> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "At one point, Tony might be in that role, and then someone else might come into that role." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ActorVsRoleAbstraction> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Roles are represented by aswritten perspectives contributed to by humans on cadence, rather than traditional full-time hires." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_TeamAsPerspectives> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Scarlet decided she does not need a co-founder, but rather a constellation of trusted partners and advisors." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_NoCoFounderNeeded> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "a centralized ground-truth holding mechanism missing from current named-perspective architecture" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_MultiRoleCoordinationGatekeeper> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "With an enterprise prospect, you don't go for the hotel. What you do is you drop the hint the first time and then you follow up with the next conversation." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_EnterpriseProspectHotelTactic> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The gatekeeper / centralized ground-truth pattern is open, not decided — does it hold truth or just route? Separate perspective or a property of the coordination plane? Resolve at run time or at memory save? Raised without a position." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_GatekeeperDesignQuestionsOpen> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_MultiRoleCoordinationGatekeeper> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Org staffing as perspectives-on-cadence and 'no co-founder, a constellation instead' is a deliberate road taken against the traditional full-time-hire / single-co-founder default." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_TeamAsPerspectives> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_NoCoFounderNeeded> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Role assignment is meant to emerge from conversation content, not static tags — and one actor can occupy many roles while one role spans many actors, resisting any one-actor-one-role compile." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ActorVsRoleAbstraction> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The practitioner case breaks the marketplace norm of one participant = one role: same account is simultaneously supplier, customer, and unpaid trust node, forcing tier design to accommodate fluid role-switching." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_PractitionerThreeRoles> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Sales-role mechanics split concretely: Tony does influence sales (warm intros, the hotel/hint tactic with an enterprise prospect) while a demo-call prospect does direct face-to-face SMB sales — same abstract role, divergent actor behavior." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_DemoProspectVsTonyDivision> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_EnterpriseProspectHotelTactic> ] ;
    narr:writer "claude (subscription)" .
}